    Request, Byteable, ProtocolEvent<ReconfigurationPacket.PacketType,java.lang.String>, ThresholdProtocolEvent<java.net.InetSocketAddress,ReconfigurationPacket.PacketType,java.lang.String>, ReconfiguratorRequest, Keyable<java.lang.String>, Summarizable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActiveReplicaError, CreateServiceName, DeleteServiceName, RequestActiveReplicas

    public abstract class ClientReconfigurationPacket
extends BasicReconfigurationPacket<java.net.InetSocketAddress>
implements ReconfiguratorRequest
    Author:
    V. Arun This abstract class is the parent class for all packets that go back and forth between clients and reconfigurators. The current instantiations of this class include CreateServiceName, DeleteServiceName, and RequestActiveReplicas. The same implementation of ClientReconfigurationPacket is used for both the request and the corresponding response. The method isRequest() says whether the packet is an incoming request or an outgoing response.
